[h1]Eclectic Traditions[/h1]

Foreign sages at the high table. A Greek physician arguing with a desert ascetic. The old ways are safe, but they are no longer the only ways.

[h2]What it does[/h2]
A new societal tradition: tradition cap +20, cultural acceptance gain +10%. An independent ruler may take it via the [b]Open the Hall to Foreign Customs[/b] decision (1000 gold, 2000 prestige, 1000 piety).

[h2]Consequences[/h2]
[list]
[*] Every direct vassal of your culture: -15 opinion against you for five years.
[*] The loudest same-culture traditionalist (zealous, stubborn, or paranoid) becomes your rival.
[*] The event window offers a "Close the doors" back-out that refunds the cost in full.
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
CK3 1.19. Does not edit vanilla files.
